It means one task is depending on another task 

To install and start apache 



---
- hosts: all
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: install apache web server
      yum:
        name: httpd
        state: present

    - name: ensure apache is started
      service:
        name: httpd
        state: started



 ansible-playbook playbook1.yml

To check status 

ansible all -a "systemctl status httpd"

To stop the service 

ansible all -m service -a "name=httpd state=stopped" -b

To uninstall 

ansible all -m yum -a "name=httpd state=absent" -b

To uninstall using sed command 

 sed -i 's/present/absent/g' playbook1.yml

Cat playbook1.yml
